benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId} - Transfer a bundle to another account

covered: Valid Payload / successful creation scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05, TC26, TC27, TC29, TC30, TC18)
Invalid Payload and Validation scenarios (TC08, TC09, TC10, TC15, TC16)
Error handling scenarios (TC06, TC07, TC13, TC14, TC24, TC25, TC24)
Edge cases (TC17, TC18, TC19, TC20, TC21, TC22, TC23, TC25)
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets (not applicable to a single bundle transfer, but guideline mentions pagination for large datasets)
Caching behavior testing (ETag / Cache-Control headers) is not covered
Rate limiting / throttling tests (no explicit tests for burst or rate limiting)
Duplicate submission handling (no explicit test ensuring idempotency or handling of repeated identical requests)
Detailed validation of all optional parameter combinations (while TC02 covers many, some combinations may be uncovered)
Detailed response content validation for all error scenarios (only some error messages are asserted)
recommendations: Add a dedicated test for idempotency / duplicate submissions to ensure the system handles repeated requests gracefully (e.g., same bundleId + targetAccountId).
Introduce tests for rate limiting / throttling behavior under high request volume.
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) to ensure proper caching behavior where applicable.
If pagination is relevant in related endpoints or future data sets, include a pagination test for large results; currently not strictly needed for a single transfer but aligns with guidelines.
Enhance error response validation to cover more machine-readable error codes alongside human-readable messages for all common failure modes.
